{
  "texts": [
    "Additional Results.We also measure the average per-task variability (std.",
    "over the performance of the four considered encodings).",
    "gpt-oss models attain the lowest variability (5.41% for -20B, 3.45% for -120B), followed by Qwen's (5.98% for -3B, 5.86% for -7B) and G1's (9.69% for -3B, 10.51% for -7B).",
    "We note that this is mostly attributed to PyG, an encoding these fine-tuned models particularly struggle with.Testing generalization on spectral tasks.",
    "Spectral quantities are fundamental for analyzing robustness and diffusion in real-world networks (Jamakovic and Van Mieghem 2008; Van Mieghem 2023; Matzner et al. 2024; Ahuja et al."
  ]
}